# Himachal Pradesh RURAL

Data is not presented where sample size is insufficient.

## Arithmetic

ASER assessments are conducted in the household. The type of school in which children are enrolled (government or private) is also recorded.

### Table 7: % Children by grade and arithmetic level
All children 2016

| Std | Cannot do subtraction | Can do subtraction | Can do division | Can do multiplication | Can do Std V level word problem | Total |
|-----|-----------------------|--------------------|-----------------|-----------------------|---------------------------------|-------|
| I   | 83.3                  | 16.7               | 0.0             | 0.0                   | 0.0                             | 100   |
| II  | 43.2                  | 56.8               | 0.0             | 0.0                   | 0.0                             | 100   |
| III | 15.5                  | 84.5               | 0.0             | 0.0                   | 0.0                             | 100   |
| IV  | 5.6                   | 94.4               | 0.0             | 0.0                   | 0.0                             | 100   |
| V   | 1.3                   | 98.7               | 0.0             | 0.0                   | 0.0                             | 100   |
| VI  | 1.3                   | 98.7               | 0.0             | 0.0                   | 0.0                             | 100   |
| VII | 0.0                   | 100.0              | 0.0             | 0.0                   | 0.0                             | 100   |
| VIII| 0.0                   | 100.0              | 0.0             | 0.0                   | 0.0                             | 100   |

Each row shows the variation in children's arithmetic levels within a given grade. For example, among children in Std III, 15.5% cannot even do subtraction, 84.5% can do subtraction but not division or higher, and 0% can do division or higher. For each grade, the total of these exclusive categories is 100%.

### Table 8: Trends over time
Arithmetic in Std III by school type
2010, 2012, 2014 and 2016

| Year | % Children in Std III who can do division |  |  |
|------|-------------------------------------------|---|---|
|      | Govt. | Pvt. | Govt. & Pvt.* |
| 2010 | 0.0   | 0.0  | 0.0           |
| 2012 | 0.0   | 0.0  | 0.0           |
| 2014 | 0.0   | 0.0  | 0.0           |
| 2016 | 0.0   | 0.0  | 0.0           |

* This is the weighted average for children in government and private schools only.

The highest level in the ASER arithmetic assessment for Std III is division. Table 8 shows the proportion of children in Std III who can do division. This figure is a proxy for "grade level" arithmetic for Std III. Data for children enrolled in government schools and private schools is shown separately.

### Table 9: Trends over time
Arithmetic in Std V and Std VIII by school type
2010, 2012, 2014 and 2016

| Year | % Children in Std V who can do multiplication |  |  | % Children in Std VIII who can do Std V level word problem |  |  |
|------|-----------------------------------------------|---|---|------------------------------------------------------------|---|---|
|      | Govt. | Pvt. | Govt. & Pvt.* | Govt. | Pvt. | Govt. & Pvt.* |
| 2010 | 75.7  | 82.8 | 77.4        | 93.2  | 92.9 | 93.1          |
| 2012 | 71.2  | 76.9 | 72.8        | 88.9  | 94.6 | 90.1          |
| 2014 | 71.5  | 82.5 | 75.3        | 90.5  | 94.8 | 91.9          |
| 2016 | 65.3  | 78.0 | 70.5        | 84.9  | 94.9 | 87.9          |

* This is the weighted average for children in government and private schools only.

### Arithmetic Tool

**Std V level word problem**

राम ने 12 सेब खरीदे। उसने 5 सेब अपने दोस्तों को दे दिए। अब उसके पास कितने सेब बचे?

**Multiplication**

$12 \times 3 =$

**Division**

$12 \div 3 =$

**Subtraction**

$12 - 3 =$

